14:["$","h2",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:3:props:style","children":"What We Like About Trex Transcend"}]
15:["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.2rem","fontWeight":600,"margin":"1.5rem 0 0.5rem"},"children":"1. The Wood Grain Is Genuinely Convincing"}]
16:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"Transcend boards feature a deep, multi-tonal grain pattern that photographs beautifully and looks natural at normal viewing distance. The Havana Gold and Spiced Rum colors, in particular, have a warmth that pairs perfectly with the red brick and stone colonial architecture that dominates Loudoun and Fairfax counties. Compared to the earlier Trex Select (now discontinued) or even the current Enhance line, Transcend is a significant step up in realism."}]
17:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"2. The Shell Protection Actually Works"}]
18:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"Trex's three-sided shell technology wraps the board's top and sides in a protective polymer cap. After 5+ years on our earliest Northern Virginia installs, we've seen zero cap delamination, zero mold penetration through the cap, and no structural degradation. Virginia's freeze-thaw cycles (30+ per winter), summer humidity, and intense UV don't faze this product. The shell does what Trex says it does."}]
19:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"3. The Color Palette Is Designed for Mid-Atlantic Architecture"}]
1a:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"Transcend offers 8 colors across two sub-collections. Our most-installed colors in Northern Virginia:"}]
