"children":["(","10%"," of our installs)"]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"0.9rem","color":"#555","lineHeight":1.5,"margin":0},"children":"Deep charcoal brown. Dramatic and modern. Gets hottest in sun — best for shaded decks."}]]}]]}]
1c:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"4. Installation Is Consistent and Predictable"}]
1d:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"From a contractor's perspective, Transcend boards are dimensionally stable, cut cleanly with standard carbide-tipped blades, and the hidden fastener system (Trex Hideaway) seats reliably. Board-to-board color consistency is excellent within a lot. We rarely encounter warped or defective boards — Trex's quality control is among the best in the industry."}]
1e:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"5. The Price-to-Performance Ratio Is Unmatched"}]
1f:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["At ",["$","$L41",null,{"href":"/composite-deck-cost-northern-virginia","style":{"color":"var(--color-primary)","fontWeight":600},"children":"$$45–$65 per square foot installed"}]," in Northern Virginia, Transcend delivers 90% of the aesthetics and 100% of the durability of products costing 15–25% more (TimberTech AZEK, Trex Lineage). For homeowners who want premium without ultra-premium pricing, it's the mathematical sweet spot."]}]
20:["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.8rem","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"1.5rem","marginTop":"2.5rem"},"children":"What We Don't Like About Trex Transcend"}]
21:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"1. Dark Colors Get Hot — Really Hot"}]
22:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["This is the single most common complaint we hear from homeowners after installation. In direct Virginia summer sun (June–August), dark Transcend colors like Lava Rock and Spiced Rum can reach ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"130–150°F"}]," surface temperature. That's too hot for bare feet. Lighter colors (Island Mist, Rope Swing) are noticeably cooler — typically 15–20 degrees lower."]}]
23:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Our recommendation:"}]," If your deck gets full afternoon sun and your family goes barefoot, choose Island Mist or Rope Swing. For pool decks, consider ",["$","$L41",null,{"href":"/trex-vs-timbertech-vs-azek","style":{"color":"var(--color-primary)","fontWeight":600},"children":"TimberTech AZEK"}]," which runs slightly cooler due to its full PVC construction."]}]
24:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"2. Light Scratches From Furniture"}]
25:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"Dragging heavy metal furniture across Transcend can leave light scuff marks on the shell surface. These are cosmetic only — they don't penetrate the protective cap — and they tend to blend into the grain pattern over a few months of UV exposure. But it's worth knowing upfront. Use furniture pads on chair and table legs."}]
26:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"3. The 25-Year Warranty Is Good, Not Great"}]
27:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"Trex Transcend carries a 25-year fade and stain warranty plus a lifetime limited structural warranty. This is solid — but Trex Lineage and TimberTech AZEK now offer 50-year warranties. If you plan to stay in your home for 25+ years or want maximum future-proofing, the 50-year warranty products are worth the 10–15% premium."}]
28:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$15:props:style","children":"4. It's Not Immune to Mold ON the Surface"}]
29:["$","p",null,{"style":"$6:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["Trex's shell prevents mold from growing ",["$","em",null,{"children":"inside"}]," the board, but organic matter (pollen, leaf debris, dirt) that sits on the surface can develop surface mold in Virginia's humid climate. This is easily solved with a biannual soap-and-water scrub. It's not a product defect — it happens on every composite brand — but homeowners who expect literally zero maintenance may be disappointed."]}]
